\cb5 [insert image here]\cb1 \
\cb5 The Government of Montserrat tried to negotiate more money from the UK to handle the volcanic crisis, but it fell on deaf ears: then Secretary for International Development, Clare Short, fumed that the riots were just little shows in the streets to get the UK spend more money on them ("They will be wanting golden elephants next"). Meanwhile, the sense of social injustice grew on island...\cb1 \
